SIMPLE: towards
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Towards
<hw>To"wards</hw> }</mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>prep.</pos><ety>[AS. <?/ impending, imminent, future, toward, <?/
towards. See <er>To</er>, and -<er>ward</er>, <er>wards</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>In the direction of; to.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He set his face <qex>toward</qex> the wilderness.</q>
<rj><qau>Num. xxiv. 1.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The waves make <qex>towards</qex> the pebbled shore.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>With direction to, in a moral sense; with respect or
reference to; regarding; concerning.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His eye shall be evil <qex>toward</qex> his brother.</q>
<rj><qau>Deut. xxviii. 54.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Herein do I exercise myself, to have always a conscience void of
offense <qex>toward</qex> God, and <qex>toward</qex> men.</q>
<rj><qau>Acts xxiv. 16.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Tending to; in the direction of; in behalf
of.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This was the first alarm England received <qex>towards</qex> any
trouble.</q> <rj><qau>Clarendom.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Near; about; approaching to.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I am <qex>toward</qex> nine years older since I left you.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Towards</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Toward</ent>⟦br⟧
<mhw>{

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Towards
<hw>To"wards</hw> }</mhw> <pos>adv.</pos>
<def>Near; at hand; in state of preparation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Do you hear sught, sir, of a battle <qex>toward</qex> ?</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We have a trifling foolish banquet <qex>Towards</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Toward</ent>⟦br⟧

